description.narrative: 1. 20.000 internally displaced persons and returnees have increased awareness about the risks of Explosive Remnants of War (ERW) and Improvised Explosive Devices (IED). 2. Areas prioritized and tasked by the Libyan Mine Action Center to DCA have been cleared of ERW and IED/Booby-traps. 3. Public safety increased, access improved for the population, and knowledge of the dangers of ERW and Booby-trap/IEDs increased from a baseline of almost zero.
DCA will deliver a phased intervention to support the stabilization of Sirte and assist people from the city and surrounding areas with their urgent needs.
